<br>
I used the helm of Rile until i gain a Froglok crown, i tried to do the helm quest but the bugger only spawns once an hour for about 5seconds, i spent about a week there RL trying to get him, finally gave up on it and just got the rile helm for free, just zoned into kc and asked if anyone was selling one. picked it up for less then it cost to make a cab scale helm.<br>
<br>
For the Pauldron, **bring a druid** i spend 30hrs just foraging for the moss, a druid friend took pity on me and stopped by not 30secs after she zoned in she foraged it, might have been just lucky but.. ya never know..  also if your doing this quest your gonna want to make sure your brewing and cooking are both above adverage, and at this point your smithing should also be there as you need a master level to make your mancatcher.  The ice is in the mountains HIGH above the Giant fortress there, its a ground spawn on a 5min timmer, there is no argo up there just make sure your a good climber or you have some form of levitation to get back down.. as its a 10k fall from up there. That fall kinda brused my tail a little bit..<br>
<br>
For the Vembraces.. just camp the building outside of the goblin fort in the woods on the same side as the field of bone is.  it may take a little while but you can also get a decent earring there if you keep the outbuilding cleared, only 2 or 3 spawns i think.. just bring along someone to help you stay alive, and keep ya company 20-30 min respawn i think..<br>
<br>
For the Breastplate, your going to have to ask another Legionnaire, as I never compleated that quest, I just ran to the Sarnak fort in the Burning Woods little building near there can find a treeweave, half the time the dru or nec there let them rott or sell them for cheep i traded a set of small banded for it.<br>
<br>
For the Greaves, the tome drops in the lake,  in the heart of the fortress  there you can get the iron bound tomb a decent group of mid 20's to early 30's should be able to hold the room, i know there were 2 groups fighting there when i was there, us and another &quot;group&quot; working on there key quest.. the book drops from the same mob, so can always ask them if they got an extra and make sure you let them know that its for a quest, offer a little something to take it of there hands.. be it just a glass of our finest green death ... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
For the Guantlets you gotta drop Blackhand in the Field down in a cave near the waters hes a rogue and WILL stab you in the back if your go to run from him ( i tried at 20... OUCH)  but i asked a nice shadow knight(49) that was working on cab faction.. (about a year and half ago, so was actually wanting to help us not rob our people) anyway she had no problem with him, i havnt gone back to see how tough he is but i think tiss low 30's..<br>
<br>
For the Gauntlets, i would reccomend taking a good group into dalnar (all of us iksar have quests in there) i dont really remember where he is as i bought a trooper bracer and had bracer of scavenging(Sp) i went back when i hit 40 with my friends mage she killed the entire zone and i found it on one of the corpses, i think was near the exit.. sorry.<br>
<br>
The boots were a pain in the tail, i tried a couple time at 36 to kill the guy but he was to tough solo, so i snaged a group of mid 30's from the fort (lots of healers for some reason...) and we took out the cave with no losses, course the high priestess that was there watching over the ranger that was with us..<br>
<br>
One word of advice though do not try to solo these quests.. bring a partner at least as i didnt and went from 35 --33--36--32 (got frustreated and kept charging back in)<br>
<br>
~Ssisal Cabiliss~<br>
Smith and Legionnare of New Sebiliss<br>
